I will not have time to look into this too soon as I will have to reinstall OSX on VirtualBox (and it's always a pain) but it's good to know the nature of this issue has been revealed. Speaking of which, this same function is defined multiple times for basically all UNIXes. It would be nice to refactor it and define it in one place only (`_psutil_posix.c`). Also, I believe it should look more or less like this:

```
/*
 * Return 1 if PID exists in the current process list, else 0, -1
 * on error.
 * TODO: this should live in _psutil_posix.c but for some reason if I
 * move it there I get a "include undefined symbol" error.
 */
int
psutil_pid_exists(long pid) {
    int ret;
    if (pid < 0)
        return 0;
    ret = kill(pid , 0);
    if (ret == 0)
        return 1;
    else {
        if (ret == ESRCH) {
            // ESRCH == No such process
            return 0;
       }
        else if ((ret == EPERM) || (ret == EACCES)) {
            // EPERM / EACCES clearly means there's a process to deny access to
            return 1;
        }
        else {
            PyErr_SetFromErrno(PyExc_OSError);
            return -1;
        }
    }
}
```

