The idea is to do away with PlainText responses entirely and always wrap the speech in `<speak></speak>` tags and not give an explicit option. All responses should just be returned as SSML responses by default.  `PlainText` responses are superfluous. 

Basically,

```
def _output_speech(speech):
    try:
        xmldoc = ElementTree.fromstring(speech)
        if xmldoc.tag == 'speak':
            return {'type': 'SSML', 'ssml': speech}
    except ElementTree.ParseError as e:
        pass
    return {'type': 'PlainText', 'text': speech}
```

would better be

```
def _output_speech(speech):
    return {'type': 'SSML', 'ssml': speech}
```

